elopment Goals; the blending of public- and private-sector investment; tensions among charitable, political, and commercial considerations. The list goes on. De Haan incorporates these factors in a succinct overview that is an ideal introduction for students encountering the subject of development for the first time, as well as a handy overview for development practitioners.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDevelopment economics. 0aEconomic assistancexInternational cooperation. 0aEconomic assistancezDeveloping countries. 0aInternational economic relations. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Economic Development.2bisacsh  aSustainable Development Goals, SDGs, foreign assistance.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishz978311131907008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2023z9783111318134oZDB-23-DBV08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107977010 cprintz978195505589540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168585280140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781685852801423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781685852801/original  a978-3-11-079770-1  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131907-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DBVb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023